> Did you know that the average worker bee produces only 1/12 teaspoon of honey in a lifetime? This means we have a whole lot of bees (and our brilliant chefs, of course) to thank for the sweet and herby pan sauce that's generously drizzled on top of tender pork. Oh—and there's also a touch of the sweet stuff in the salad dressing, so expect to be licking your lips after every bite.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel the @shallot{1}. Thinly slice one half and mince the other. Strip the @thyme{1/4%oz} of the sprigs before roughly chopping the leaves. Halve, pit, and slice the @peach{1}(halved and pitted) into wedges.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @honey{1/2%tsp}, @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp}, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%tsp} (to taste). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Couscous ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add the minced shallot. Cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add @water{1%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil. Once boiling, add the @couscous{1/2%cup}, cover, and remove from heat until the rest of the meal is ready.

== Pork Chops and Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @boneless pork chops{12%oz} on all sides with salt and pepper before adding them to the pan. Cook ~{3-4%minutes} per side, or until cooked to desired doneness. Remove from pan and set aside to rest ~{5%minutes} before thinly slicing.

Add the sliced shallot and thyme to the same pan over medium heat. Cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened, adding a drizzle of olive oil if necessary. Add the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @honey{1/2%tsp}, and @water{1/2%cup} to the pan. Scrape up all the browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring to a boil and reduce until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if necessary.

== Salad and Serving ==

Toss the @arugula{2%oz} and peach wedges into the vinaigrette. Season with salt and pepper. Fluff the couscous with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Serve the pan-seared pork chops on a bed of couscous with the peach arugula salad on the side. Drizzle with the shallot thyme pan sauce and enjoy!